0B23                       1488 FORMATTAB:
0B23                       1489 ;There are 16 entries in this table. The 4-bit index is built like this:
0B23                       1490 ;	Bit 3		0 for normal memory ops, 1 if extended is OK
0B23                       1491 ;	Bit 2		0 for integer, 1 for real
0B23                       1492 ;	Bit 0 & 1	Flag: 00=W, 01=S, 10=L, 11=T
0B23                       1493 ;
0B23                       1494 ;The entries in the table are used as two 3-bit fields. Bits 0-2 are ORed
0B23                       1495 ;into the first byte of the opcode for the Memory Format field. Bits 3-6
0B23                       1496 ;are ORed into the second byte to modify the opcode for extended operands.
0B23                       1497 ;If bit 7 is set, then that combination is illegal.
